Text.SourceString: Sometimes school is boring.//<portrait=annoyed>You read all these hard books all the time. Bleh!
I saw <NpcName>Uncle Rafael</> yesterday. He came to visit us at the inn.//<portrait=annoyed>Every time I see him, he always asks me about school... Like every week!
Yeah, I play at the beach with Oliver after school.//<portrait=happy>So much fun!//<portrait=normal>But then, we get so hungry after a while, so we go home.
<NpcName>Emma</> makes really good fish tacos!//Sometimes she just comes to our class and hands them out to us for free.
She taught us how to make fish tacos, but mom already taught me first.//So I learned nothing new.
I like cats. They’re so cute and fluffy.//<portrait=happy>Especially when they purr...
<NpcName>Mr. Barnes</> said that we don't need to know what we wanna be when we grow up yet.
He also told us that sometimes adults are not sure about what they want to be either.//And that's okay...
I'm never cutting my hair.//I'm gonna grow it really long like mom's.
My mom. She always packs me lunch for school.//<portrait=doubt>She said lunch first, snacks second... Oh well.
I like to wear my hair down. Just like my mom!//<portrait=normal>And <NpcName>Aunt Alice</> too.
I’m allowed to sleep at 10 sometimes.//<portrait=doubt>But not too often, because mom and dad said that I get cranky in the morning if I stay up too often.
